&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Four panels sewn together in a diagonal pattern&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Each panel is 16.5cm/6.4in wide, 39cm/15.3in long&lt;/li>
&lt;li>With a 8mm hook, this would be 12 stitches and 32 rows&lt;/li>
&lt;li>The sewing up the sides leaves 6 rows on the top (32/6 = 5.3)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://mypicot.com/img/pt-1112.jpg"
loading="lazy"
alt="textured wave pattern"
> &lt;img src="https://mypicot.com/img/pt-3488-1.jpg"
loading="lazy"
alt="cable stitch"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>From right to left, we have the &lt;a class="link" href="https://mypicot.com/0029.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>textured wave pattern&lt;/a> (16x + 5) and the beautiful &lt;a class="link" href="https://mypicot.com/2082.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>wide cable stitch&lt;/a>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>